To create a block of equations in LaTeX, you typically use the `align`, `align*`, `equation`, or `gather` environments, depending on how you want the equations to appear (aligned, numbered, etc.). Below are some common ways to create blocks of equations in LaTeX:

### 1. Using the `align` Environment

The `align` environment allows you to align equations at a specific point (usually the equal sign). Each line is numbered by default.

```latex
\begin{align}
    a &= b + c \\
    d &= e - f
\end{align}
```

### 2. Using the `align*` Environment (Unnumbered)

To prevent numbering, use the `align*` environment:

```latex
\begin{align*}
    a &= b + c \\
    d &= e - f
\end{align*}
```

### 3. Using the `equation` Environment

The `equation` environment is used for a single numbered equation. For multiple equations, you would typically use it multiple times:

```latex
\begin{equation}
    a = b + c
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
    d = e - f
\end{equation}
```

### 4. Using the `gather` Environment

The `gather` environment centers equations on each line without alignment:

```latex
\begin{gather}
    a = b + c \\
    d = e - f
\end{gather}
```

### 5. Using `multline` for Long Equations

If you have a long equation that needs to be broken across multiple lines, you can use the `multline` environment:

```latex
\begin{multline}
    a + b + c + d + e + f + g + h + i + j + k + l + m + n + o + p \\
    = q + r + s + t + u + v + w + x + y + z
\end{multline}
```

### Putting it All Together in LaTeX

Here's a complete example that shows different methods:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{amsmath}

\begin{document}

% Aligned equations with numbering
\begin{align}
    a &= b + c \\
    d &= e - f
\end{align}

% Unnumbered aligned equations
\begin{align*}
    x &= y + z \\
    m &= n - o
\end{align*}

% Single numbered equations
\begin{equation}
    p = q + r
\end{equation}

\begin{equation}
    s = t - u
\end{equation}

% Centered equations without alignment
\begin{gather}
    v = w + x \\
    y = z - a
\end{gather}

\end{document}
```

